  "content": "ID: T1003.003\nTitle: OS Credential Dumping:NTDS\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1003/003\nAdversaries may attempt to access or create a copy of the Active Directory domain database in order to steal credential information, as well as obtain other information about domain members such as devices, users, and access rights. By default, the NTDS file (NTDS.dit) is located in %SystemRoot%\\NTDS\\Ntds.dit of a domain controller. [1] In addition to looking for NTDS files on active Domain Controllers, adversaries may search for backups that contain the same or similar information. [2] The following tools and techniques can be used to enumerate the NTDS file and the contents of the entire Active Directory hashes. Volume Shadow Copy secretsdump.py Using the in-built Windows tool, ntdsutil.exe Invoke-NinjaCopy",
  "category": "Article",
  "source": "Local Storage",
